PN,41908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1773850286
OL,3,CArchbishop of Canterbury will pray for
OL,4,C'fractured world' on six-day pilgrimage
OL,6,FThe Prince of Wales will represent the
OL,7,FKing at the historic ceremony, which
OL,8,Fwill see a woman formally take up the
OL,9,Frole for the first time in the
OL,10,FChurch's history.
OL,12,FCharles is supreme governor of the
OL,13,FChurch of England but William, his son
OL,14,Fand heir, will deputise for the head
OL,15,Fof state at the service. He will be
OL,16,Fjoined by the Princess of Wales.
OL,18,FAs the ceremony marks the official
OL,19,Fstart of Dame Sarah's public ministry,
OL,20,Fshe will, for the first time, preach a
OL,21,Fsermon as Archbishop of Canterbury.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
