OL,3,CArchbishop of Canterbury will pray for
OL,4,C'fractured world' on six-day pilgrimage
OL,6,FThe Dean of Canterbury, David
OL,7,FMonteith, is expected to join for the
OL,8,Ffinal stretch of the journey, walking
OL,9,Ffrom the village of Chartham to
OL,10,FCanterbury, and aiming to arrive in
OL,11,Ftime for evensong.
OL,13,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,14,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,15,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,16,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,17,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,18,Fbelow...
